-- Azarenka Serves 10 Double Faults in French Open Win Over Cornet
-- B y   D a n i e l l e   R o s s i n g h
-- 2013-06-01T11:36:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-01/azarenka-serves-10-double-faults-in-french-open-win-over-cornet.html
Australian Open winner Victoria
Azarenka overcame 10 double faults as she held off Alize Cornet
to move to the fourth round of the French Open.  The third-seeded Azarenka of Belarus beat the No. 31 seed
from France, 4-6, 6-3, 6-1 on the main Court Philippe Chatrier
in Paris.  Sloane Stephens, the No. 17 seed from the U.S. also moved
to the fourth round, beating New Zealand’s Marina Erakovic in
three sets.  Later today, men’s top seed  Novak Djokovic  plays Bulgaria’s
26th seed Grigor Dimitrov of Bulgaria, while defending men’s
champion Rafael Nadal of Spain faces Italy’s Fabio Fognini.
Maria Sharapova, the defending women’s champion of  Russia , plays
China’s Zheng Jie.  To contact the reporter on this story:
